Test 3.7 final and 3.8-dev on Travis and drop 3.3 (#179)

* Test 3.7 final and 3.8-dev on Travis

* Bump to Xenial to enable Python 3.7+ support

* Drop support for end-of-life Python 3.3

Patches segfault in pixa_to_list (#176)

The zip returned by cdef func pixa_to_list produces a segfault in Python 3.x, where the zip builtin is generator-based. The segfault is avoided by returned a list instead.

Add pkg-config to Debian/Ubuntu requirements

On a clean Ubuntu install you need to include ```apt install pkg-config``` before ```pip install tesserocr``` will work.
